== Solution Map ==
* '''Pulse.Web''' - ASP.NET MVC 5 web application (primary UI)
* '''Pulse.Api''' - ASP.NET Web API 2 service (data + business endpoints)
* '''Pulse.Core''' - entities and interfaces
* '''Pulse.Infrastructure''' - Oracle/Dapper data access, repositories, infra services
* '''Pulse.Services''' - business/domain services
* '''Pulse.ViewModels''' and '''Pulse.DataTransformationObjects''' - request/response shaping models
* '''pulse.react''' - React migration workspace (route-parity frontend)
* '''TableSchema''' - schema and module definitions

== Runtime Summary ==
Pulse runs as a layered .NET Framework 4.7.2 system with two runtime entry points:
* '''Pulse.Web''' for authenticated browser workflows and SignalR-backed UX patterns
* '''Pulse.Api''' for authenticated API calls (including JWT bearer flows)

== Domain Summary ==
The main domain is project and roadmap execution across plants/products/categories, including:
* project registration and roadmap snapshotting
* milestone/activity planning and task execution
* forms, comments, attachments, and audit trails
* notifications and role-based access management

== Conventions ==
* Schema owner: '''NPITRACK'''
* Data store: '''Oracle'''
* Data access style: '''Dapper / Dapper.Oracle'''
* Authorization style: module-code claims and membership-scoped access checks

